## Plan Summary

**Root cause:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts` at line 7.

```typescript
// BUG — stops one iteration early
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// FIX — processes every element
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

The `- 1` in the loop bound means for an array of `n` items, only `n-1` items are ever processed — the last element is always skipped.

**Scope:** Single-character change (`- 1` removed) in one file — `src/utils.ts` line 7. No other files need modification.

**Tests:** 3 of the 6 tests are currently failing (`processItems` with 3 items, 2 items, and 1 item). All 6 will pass after the fix.

Shall I apply the fix?

